## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the evolving nature of the COVID-19 pandemic. Variations in data collection methods and reporting standards across different regions may also affect the comparability of findings. Additionally, the emergence of new variants and changes in public health policies can influence mortality rates and vaccine effectiveness over time.